Class Shopper

java.lang.Object
com.example.mco2_supermarketsimulator.Shopper
public class Shopper extends Object
This is the class of the Shopper, where all the shopper related things happen, such as movement and interaction.

    • Shopper

      public Shopper(String name, int age, javafx.scene.image.Image image, Tile startTile)
      This is the constructor of the Shopper, it requires necessities like name and all that.
      Parameters:
      name - the name of the shopper.
      age - the age of the shopper, important for determining legalities like discounts and prohibitions.
      image - the image texture of the shopper.
      startTile - the starting position/tile of the shopper.

    • tryMoveTile

      public void tryMoveTile(int rowOffset, int colOffset, Floor floor)
      This is the prerequisite to moving the shopper. It checks if the shopper can move first. A shopper can't move continuously to another direction if they are moving already.
      Parameters:
      rowOffset - this is to know if the shopper is moving up or down.
      colOffset - this is to know if the shopper is moving left or right.
      floor - this is to know which floor the shopper is on.

    • interact

      public void interact(Supermarket supermarket, Tile chosenTile, javafx.scene.Scene scene, DisplayController displayController, ProductSearchController productSearchController)
      The shopper interaction with the tile that was chosen, such as if it is a service or a display, etc.
      Parameters:
      supermarket - the supermarket to refer to.
      chosenTile - the tile that was chosen to be interacted with.
      scene - the current scene.
      displayController - the controller for the ui of the display tiles.
      productSearchController - the controller for the ui of the checkout counter.

    • addProduct

      public boolean addProduct(Product product)
      Adding a product to the shopper's inventory from a display.
      Parameters:
      product - the product to add to the shopper.
      Returns:
      returns true if the product was successfully added, and false if otherwise.

    • removeProduct

      public void removeProduct(Product product, ArrayList<Product> products, Display currentDisplay)
      Returns a product from the shopper's inventory back to the display.
      Parameters:
      product - the product to return.
      products - the ArrayList to put back the product to.
      currentDisplay - the current display being interacted with.
